          "text": "Most automation tools expect you to be technical before you can use them.\n \nDrag-and-drop builders. Workflow logic. API documentation. Conditional branches.\n \nAnd that's before you even automate anything.\n \nTurbotic Automation AI takes a different approach.\n \nYou describe what you want in plain English:\n \n→ \"Pull last month's Stripe revenue, break it down by category, email it to leadership on the 1st of every month.\"\n \n→ \"When a new lead enters HubSpot, wait 24 hours, then send a personalized follow-up.\"\n \n→ \"Check my vendor contracts sheet daily. If anything expires within 30 days, send a Slack alert.\"\n \nTurbotic builds the automation. It asks clarifying questions if needed. It tells you exactly which API keys to connect and where to find them.\n \nThen it runs.\n \nSame process whether you're in sales, finance, marketing, ops, or IT.\n \nNo code. No workflow builders. No tutorials.\n \nJust describe the task and let it handle the rest.\n \nOver to you: What repetitive task would you automate first?",
