          "timeSincePosted": "1d",
          "shareUrn": "urn:li:ugcPost:7428004409143369728",
          "text": "I used to show up to sales calls unprepared.\n \n20 minutes before a meeting, I'd be scrambling. Googling the company. Scrolling their LinkedIn. Checking Crunchbase. Reading their blog.\n \nAnd I'd still miss something important.\n \nhere's how I prep for every sales call now using FlashLabs' SuperAgent:\n \nstep 1: go to flashlabs.ai open SuperAgent and click on \"Research\"\n \nstep 2: type one message I wrote: \"generate an account intelligence report on Acquisition\"\n \nstep 3: it goes and pulls everything on its own funding rounds, revenue signals, growth trajectory, key decision makers with their LinkedIn profiles, what they've been posting about recently, their tech stack, competitors, job openings, and likely pain points.\n \nstep 4: you get a full briefing doc not a wall of random Google results. a structured report you can skim in 2 minutes before your call.\n \nwho's who at the company. what they care about right now. and what angles make sense for your pitch.\n \nstep 5: walk into the call like you've been studying them for a week\n \nthat's it.\n \nI didn't ask an AI for advice. I gave it a task and it actually went and did the research for me. That's the difference.\n \nno tabs. no manual research. no forgetting to check something important.\n \nsave this if you take sales calls regularly :))\n \nOver to you: how do you currently prep before your sales meetings?\n \nif you want the exact prompt I used, here's the link to the chat: https://lnkd.in/eq2ii4an",
