          "text": "I was spending 30 minutes every morning scrolling through tech news sites just to stay updated.\n \nSo I built an AI agent that does it for me. It pulls news from my favorite sources, reads through everything, and sends me a clean summary every single morning.\n \nNow I consume all of that in a 5-minute email with my morning coffee.\n \nAnd I built the entire thing just by talking to AI. No code. No workflows. No node editors.\n \nI used Appy.AI, and here's what surprised me:\n \n→ I typed one sentence: \"Build me a news AI agent that monitors and summarizes daily tech news\"\n→ Their agent builder Violet started asking me clarifying questions\n→ Within minutes, it built the full application with a landing page, settings, triggers, and database\n→ It even generated a name, logo, and personalized the whole experience\n \nBut here's what really sets it apart from every other AI builder I've tried:\n \n1️⃣ Full authentication system built in. Users can sign up, log in, and manage their accounts\n2️⃣ Organization management with roles and team invites\n3️⃣ Third-party integrations like Airtable, Calendly, and your existing tool stack\n4️⃣ Scheduled triggers so my agent runs automatically every morning\n5️⃣ Built-in Stripe infrastructure so you can start charging customers immediately\n \nI connected my agent to Airtable, customized the theme to cyberpunk (because why not), and the whole thing was production-ready without touching a single line of code.\n \nYou can build agents for yourself, your team, or to sell and monetize. The entire business infrastructure is already there.\n \nThis is the first platform I've used where building and shipping the product wasn't the hard part at all.\n \nTry it yourself: https://lnkd.in/ezrHd5v5\n \nOver to you: If you could build any AI agent and start selling it tomorrow, what would it do?",
