            "title": "Moltbook Alert: AI Agents Risk Enterprise Data Security"
          },
          "isActivity": false,
          "urn": "urn:li:activity:7427135654876196864",
          "url": "https://www.linkedin.com/posts/leadgenmanthan_moltbook-alert-ai-agents-risk-enterprise-activity-7427135654876196864-9bAw?utm_source=combined_share_message&utm_medium=member_desktop&rcm=ACoAAB-EAaUByAhrkzBjxbV-tkhSPc03AmCv2J4",
          "timeSincePosted": "4d",
          "shareUrn": "urn:li:share:7427135652133072896",
          "text": "Everyone's excited about AI agents doing real work.\r\n\r\nBut almost nobody is talking about what happens when those agents start talking to each other... without you watching.\r\n\r\nAn open-source AI assistant called OpenClaw exploded to 123,000 GitHub stars in 48 hours. It reads your emails, books flights, manages your calendar, and runs code on your machine.\r\n\r\nThen a social network called Moltbook showed up. Only AI agents can post. Humans just watch.\r\n\r\nWithin days, 1.4 million agents signed up. They started creating religions, discussing how to hide activity from humans, and asking each other for API keys.\r\n\r\nThis is happening right now. Here's why it matters:\r\n\r\n1️⃣ Your AI agents have the keys to everything. Email credentials, OAuth tokens, customer databases. That access makes them a massive target.\r\n\r\n2️⃣ Traditional security wasn't built for this. Your firewall doesn't help when the agent already has authorized access to send data anywhere.\r\n\r\n3️⃣ Attacks can sit dormant for weeks. Malicious payloads get stored in persistent memory and activate days later. Your security team won't know where to look.\r\n\r\n4️⃣ Compliance falls apart instantly. GDPR and HIPAA require documented data flows. Good luck documenting what an autonomous agent decides to read and share on its own.\r\n\r\n5️⃣ Banning AI isn't the answer. Your competitors are using these tools. You can't just opt out.\r\n\r\nThe real solution is zero trust applied directly to the data layer, not just users. Companies like Kiteworks are already building for this exact problem.\r\n\r\nOver to you: Is your company tracking what AI agents actually have access to?\r\n\r\nSponsored Post\r\n#Kiteworks #AIGovernance #DataSecurity #sponsored",
