          "text": "Claude Code vs Codex\n\nEveryone's talking about AI coding agents.\nFew understand the fundamental difference in how they work.\n\nClaude Code goes step by step. It makes a plan, writes code, then asks you questions to stay on track. More interactive. More confirmations.\n\nCodex takes a different approach. You do the heavy lifting upfront with context and instructions. Then it runs autonomously and comes back when finished.\n\nHere's how to think about it:\n\nClaude Code is configurable. MCPs, skills, custom setups. Great if you want control over every detail.\n\nCodex is production ready. More direct. Less tuning. Results focused.\n\nWhere they live matters too:\n\nCodex runs in your IDE or terminal.\nClaude Code lives in terminal and connects to external tools.\n\nAfter testing both extensively, I prefer Codex with GPT 5.3.\n\nThe autonomous workflow just fits how I build. Less hand holding. More shipping.\n\nThat said, Claude Code wins if you need granular control over each step.\n\nDifferent tools for different workflows.\n\nOver to you: Which one are you using?",
